      <description>&lt;div class=&#39;shortcode-quote w3-panel w3-leftbar w3-theme-l3  &#39;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;i class=&#39;fas fa-quote-right w3-xxlarge&#39;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#39;&#39;&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can extend Hugoâ€™s built-in shortcodes by creating your own using&#xA;the same templating syntax as that for single and list pages.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Shortcodes are a means to consolidate templating into small, reusable&#xA;snippets that you can embed directly inside of your content. In this&#xA;sense, you can think of shortcodes as the intermediary between page&#xA;and list templates and basic content files.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&#39;shortcode-quote-source&#39;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io/templates/shortcode-templates&#34;&gt;https://gohugo.io/templates/shortcode-templates&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;shortcodes-in-this-theme-for-w3css-classes&#34;&gt;Shortcodes in this Theme for W3.CSS classes&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;alert&#34;&gt;alert&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Inspired by &lt;a href=&#34;http://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.0/components/alerts/&#34;&gt;http://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.0/components/alerts/&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.w3schools.com/w3css/w3css_panels.asp&#34;&gt;https://www.w3schools.com/w3css/w3css_panels.asp&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Configuration is in &lt;code&gt;params.toml&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
